						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Pillar in the Raṅga-maṇḍapa of the Yellamma temple on the Yellamma hill near Saundatti</hi></p>						

						<p>Sadās11ivarāya—A.D. 1560.</p>						

						<p>This badly damaged and worn out record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1482, Dundubhi, Chaitra śu 1.</hi> The date is irregular. The year Dundubhi coincided with Śaka 1484 and not 1482. Since no weekday is given, the date is not verifiable. Taking the Śaka year to be correct, it may be equated with <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1560, March 27, Wednesday.</hi></p>						

						<p>The inscription seems to record a gift of land by Viṭhapa, the secretary <hi rend="italic">(kāryakartta)</hi> of Venkaṭādrirājayya, who probably obtained the gift from Mahāmaṇḍalēśvara <hi rend="bold">Rāmarājayya.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
